For the purpose of this query, a high rating is determined by an average course rating of 4 or above; 
Positive feedback is any rating of 4 or 5; 
Negative feedback is any rating of 1 or 2; 
Active enrollment indicates a student is currently participating in the course; 
Dropped enrollment indicates a student has stopped participating but was once active; 
Withdrawn enrollment indicates a student has officially withdrawn from the course.

sql:
SELECT announcement_title, announcement_content
FROM course_announcements
WHERE important = 1;

SELECT MAX(announcement_date) AS latest_announcement_date
FROM course_announcements
WHERE course_id = 1;

SELECT course_title
FROM courses
WHERE course_id IN (SELECT course_id FROM prerequisites);
